      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Living constitutionalism is inherently subjective because it allows judges to reinterpret foundational texts based on contemporary societal values. While it claims flexibility, this flexibility is a backdoor for judicial policymaking, allowing judges to substitute their personal moral views for the established law. Originalism, by contrast, provides a fixed, objective anchor to prevent the judiciary from becoming a political super-legislature.",
      "source": "target",
